            <!-- end card container #3  -->





            <!-- Card container #3-->
            <div class="card__container">
              <!-- Card -->
              <div class="card">
                <!-- Front side -->
                <div class="side side__front">
                      <img src="assets/images/blackwhite/owl.jpg" alt="">
                </div>
                <!-- end front side  -->
                <div class="side side__back">
                  <div class="col">
                    <div class="content">
                      <div class="text">
                          <div style="overflow:auto; overflow-x:hidden; height: 100px;">
                          <a href="http://pooool.info/u-mad-bro-direct-action-in-the-meme-pool/?key=22206"> U MAD BRO? </a>
                        <p>
                          This structure in itself is reminiscent of prefigurative politics[1]; it is a “temporary autonomous zone”, a term coined by anarchist philosopher Hakim Bey, described as an ephemeral utopia site which eludes traditional dynamics of law and hierarchy. Like Bey’s idea of a temporary autonomous zone, 4chan has no imposing will (short of rules against child pornography) and participants act without regulation or dictation from a command-hierarchy. It is unlikely that there was such a precise ideological motivation behind the creation of 4chan, rather this is an evolving potential that it holds in a broader, highly politicized meme pool.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                        <br>
                        <br>
                                   ___________________________

                        <br>
                        <br>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
