                      <img src="assets/images/strawberry.jpg" alt="">
                </div>
                <!-- end front side  -->
                <div class="side side__back">
                  <div class="col">
                    <div class="content">
                      <div class="text">
                          <div style="overflow:auto; overflow-x:hidden; height: 100px;">
                        <a href="http://dpub.uriahgray.com/content/4-library/davison-thelanguageofinternetmemes.pdf?key=25157"> THE LANGUAGE OF INTERNET MEMES</a>
                        <p>
                          Emoticons are a meme that serve a number of functions in the transmission
  of information. Tey can be used to frame content as positive or negative,
  serious or joking, or any number of other things. Hamster Dance essentially
  serves a single function: to entertain. Tis diference in function infuences the
  primary modes of access for each of these memes. For the emoticon meme the
  behavior is to construct any number of emotional glyphs in any number of settings,
  while for the Hamster Dance meme the behavior is only a single thing:
  have people (themselves or others) view the Hamster Dance web page. Te
  Hamster Dance page is a singular thing, a spectacle. It gains infuence through
  its surprising centralization. It is a piece of content that seems unsuited given
  more traditional models of assessment of organizing people around a central
  location, but yet, that is precisely the function it serves.
  Emoticons gain infuence in exactly the opposite way. Tere was an original,
  single emoticon typed in 1982, but other emoticons do not drive people
  toward that single iteration. Te emoticon has gained infuence not by
  being surprisingly centralized but by being surprisingly distributed. Hamster
  Dance is big like Mt. Rushmore. Emoticons are big like McDonald’s. Tis
  frst distinction, then, is that the infuence gained by memes can be both centralized
  and distributed.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                        <br>
                        <br>
                                   ___________________________

                        <br>
                        <br>
                      </div>
                    </div>
